coverage could involve parsing and command construction. However, for Maven SCM, if a commit is generated, I might need to set environment variables for user identity properly. If this is neglected, the git executable will fail during integrations.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating git configuration for tests**\\n\\nI'm considering the setup choices for running tests that execute git commits in a temporary repository. It seems I might need to configure the git identity there, but it’s not strictly necessary. To properly call `checkIn`, the identity must be set, although I could avoid this check or configure the repository directly in the test code. I might need to look at upstream tests for any prerequisites, especially for maven-scm git tests that work with local repositories without Docker. It's worth inspecting the source jar for better insights!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_QAkGiXsSg1EbcHFG0Dzs8Gsy|fc_0f71aa7f4ac1cdd2016a294c0cfc1c8194b77ec05f27c02b5e", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "tmp=$(mktemp -d)\npython3 - <<'PY' \"$tmp\"\nimport sys, urllib.request, os\nfor art in ['maven-scm-provider-gitexe','maven-scm-provider-gittest','maven-scm-test']:\n for cls in ['-sources.jar','.jar']:\n  url=f'https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/apache/maven/scm/{art}/2.0.0/{art}-2.0.0{cls if cls.startswith(\"-\") else \"\"}'\nPY\n# simpler\npython3 - <<'PY' \"$tmp\"\nimport urllib.request, os, sys\nfor art in ['maven-scm-provider-gitexe','maven-scm-provider-gittest','maven-scm-test']:\n url=f'https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/apache/maven/scm/{art}/2.0.0/{art}-2.0.0-sources.jar'\n try:\n  p=os.path.join(sys.argv[1],art+'-sources.jar'); urllib.request.urlretrieve(url,p); print(p)\n except Exception as e: print('ERR',url,e)\nPY\nfor j in \"$tmp\"/*sources.jar; do echo \"--- $(basename $j)\"; jar tf \"$j\" | grep -E 'Test.java|Git.*Command|Abstract.*Tck|ScmTestCase' | head -80; done", "timeout": 60}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider":